An Ejigbo Magistrates’ Court has arraigned a teenager identified as Mustapha Abdullahi, for allegedly stealing a cable worth N75,000 from a transformer, NAN reports.  The 19-year old, residing in the Igando area of Lagos, faces one count charge of stealing. The prosecutor, Insp. Benedict Aigbokhan, said the felony happened on December 24, 2021, at Oje Olorunfemi Street, Egan, Igando. The police officer told the court that Abdullahi’s action threw the community into darkness. The theft of the cable, an Ikeja Electric Distribution Company (IKEDC) property, contravened Section 287 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The section provides three years imprisonment for the offence. Abdullahi pleaded not guilty to the charge. The Magistrate, Mr E. O. Ogunkanmi, granted him N100,000 bail. The defendant must providesureties employed; they must show evidence of tax payment to the Lagos State Government. The case was adjourned until February 21 for further hearing.   By Deborah Akpede Lagos  -   A 29-year-old employee of  Ikeja Electricity Distribution Company (IKEDC),  Gbemisola Olaleye, who allegedly stole his employer’s N1.4 million and also forged some documents, was on Tuesday released on a N500,000 bail. The woman, whose address was not provided, was released on bail after she entered… In "Business" By Deborah Akpede   Ikeja,   -     A 52-year-old man, Henry Anuwom, was docked at an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court on Wednesday for allegedly using a cutlass to attack a staff member of Ikeja Electricity Distribution Company (IKEDC) . Anuwom was alleged to have used a cutlass to cut… In "Metro" By Adaeze Iroha Lagos - Two men who allegedly beat up two Ikeja Electricity Distribution Company (IKEDC) officials for disconnecting their electricity supply were on Thursday brought in a Yaba Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos. The police charged Godwin Owen; 42, and Valentine Brown; 38, with counts of breach of… In "Metro"